    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-15T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-15T03:00:00-05:00" n="696"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">694.001/8–1551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser to <gloss
                            target="#t_SCAP1">SCAP</gloss>
                    </hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sebald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-15T18:00:00+10:00"
                            >August 15, 1951—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Topad1">Topad</gloss> 330. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 229, Aug 10.<note n="1" xml:id="d696fn1">Not printed. In it
                        was transmitted the text of the security treaty draft of July 31, <ref
                            target="#pg_1233">p. 1233</ref>.</note> Authentic text security treaty
                    transmitted <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>, which has submitted fol
                    comments under date Aug 15:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Begin text</hi>. Fol points concerning formalities are
                    suggested to US Govt for its consideration: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>After word “accordingly”, following words be added: “the two countries
                            have agreed as follows:”</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Instead of depositing instruments of ratification, they wld be
                            exchanged at Washington. Exchange of ratification is internationally
                            established practice in case bilateral treaties.</item>
                        <pb facs="1292" n="1274" xml:id="pg_1274"/>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Usual finishing clause reading as follows be added: “in faith thereof
                            the undersigned plenipotentiaries have signed the present treaty. Done
                            at (blank) this (blank) day of (blank) 1951, in duplicate in the English
                            and Japanese languages”.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Paras 1 to 5 might better be named Article 1, Article 2, etc., as they
                            are so referred to in text.<note n="2" xml:id="d696fn2">In telegram 263
                                of August 16, drafted by Mr. Dulles, the Department replied as
                                follows: “We accept the four points and will cable text clause
                                dealing with exchange ratifications.” (694.001/8–1651)</note>
                            <hi rend="italic">End text.</hi>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Jap translation security treaty being airpouched.</p>
                <p>Substance <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 220, Aug 9<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d696fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1252">p. 1252</ref>.</note>
                    communicated informally to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> August
                    10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sebald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
